🧠 1. Cache Coherency
MSI, MESI, MOESI , MOSI are hardware based coherency right ?
Whereas Snooping and Directory based coherency are software based coherency. right ?

Good instinct to categorize — but this specific classification is not correct. Let’s fix it cleanly 👇

❌ Your statement (why it’s wrong)

“MSI/MESI/MOESI/MOSI are hardware-based,
Snooping/Directory are software-based”

👉 The issue:

Snooping and Directory are NOT software-based
They are also hardware mechanisms
🧠 Correct Classification (VERY IMPORTANT)

You need to separate two different layers:

🧩 1️⃣ Coherency Protocols (Rules)

👉 These define what should happen

Examples:

MESI protocol
MSI, MOESI, MOSI
🧠 They specify:
States (Modified, Shared, etc.)
State transitions
Ownership rules

👉 ✔ Always implemented in hardware

🧩 2️⃣ Coherency Mechanisms (How rules are enforced)

👉 These define how communication happens

🔹 Snooping
Broadcast-based
All caches monitor bus
🔹 Directory-based
Central tracking
Targeted communication

👉 ✔ Also implemented in hardware

🎯 So the correct mapping is:
Category	Examples	Role	Implementation
Protocol (rules)	MSI, MESI, MOESI	Define behavior	Hardware
Mechanism (communication)	Snooping, Directory	Enforce behavior	Hardware
🔥 Where does SOFTWARE coherency exist?

👉 Only in systems where:

No hardware protocol exists
Software explicitly manages:
Flush
Invalidate
Synchronization
Example:
DMA buffers
Some embedded systems
GPU memory management
⚠️ Key Insight

👉 Snooping/Directory ≠ software
👉 They are just different hardware architectures for implementing coherency

🧠 Clean mental model

👉 Think:

Protocol = laws
Mechanism = how police enforce laws

Both are part of hardware system

💡 One-line correct answer

MSI, MESI, MOESI, and MOSI are hardware coherency protocols, while snooping and directory-based approaches are hardware mechanisms used to implement these protocols. Software-based coherency is separate and involves explicit cache management.

🔥 This is a VERY common interview trap

Many people mix:

Protocol vs mechanism
Hardware vs software

👉 You won’t now 😄
